# graphify-only override of .gitignore.
#
# .gitignore intentionally excludes per-run /propuesta output
# (proposal/scoping/, vault/secciones/*, vault/insumos/*) from git tracking
# so a real run never gets committed by accident. graphify's detect() merges
# .gitignore into its own ignore rules by default, which meant every
# `graphify papers/` (Fase 1a/1b) and `graphify .` (vault graph) call in the
# /propuesta pipeline silently scanned 0 files — the corpus was always
# "ignored" before graphify ever looked at it.
#
# These negations are read after .gitignore in the same directory and win
# under last-match-wins semantics, so they un-ignore these paths for
# graphify's own view WITHOUT touching git tracking at all — .gitignore is
# unchanged, these directories remain untracked/uncommitted.
!proposal/scoping/
!proposal/scoping/**
!vault/secciones/
!vault/secciones/**
!vault/insumos/
!vault/insumos/**

# The blanket negations above also resurrect vault/secciones/.obsidian/
# (Obsidian's local app-state dir, separately excluded by .gitignore's
# top-level `.obsidian/` rule) — re-exclude it explicitly, it is noise,
# not content.
vault/secciones/.obsidian/
vault/secciones/.obsidian/**
